com.parse4cn1

Class ParseObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.parse4cn1.ParseObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parse.IPersistable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParseInstallation, ParseRole, ParseUser

    public class ParseObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements Parse.IPersistable
    The ParseObject is a local representation of data that can be saved and retrieved from the Parse cloud.

    The basic workflow for creating new data is to construct a new ParseObject, use put(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object) to fill it with data, and then use save() to persist to the cloud.

    The basic workflow for accessing existing data is to use a ParseQuery to specify which existing data to retrieve.

    ParseObjects are Externalizable, i.e., they can be converted to an externalizable form via asExternalizable().

    Note: The Parse backend always stores and returns UTC dates so the time zone information in any Date objects should be ignored and all dates retrived from Parse or sent to Parse should be in UTC.
